{"name":"Elemental Affinity: Water (Shifting)","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/waterfall.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Branching Elements:</strong> Ice or Blood</p><p><em>A person in-tune with Water may be sensitive, unsocial, imaginative, intuitive, artistic, and emotional. They potentially can be secretive, but also empathetic.</em></p><p>Your Armor becomes 12 + Dexterity Modifier</p><p><strong>Roll to Resist Proficiency:</strong> Resist Magic Proficiency</p><p><strong>Elemental Affinity (Skill Mastery):</strong> Your connection with your Element empowers you to recognize your strengths and grants confidence in yourself and a Skill. After choosing your Element, choose either a Skill you gained Proficiency in from your Court Card of Fate or one Proficiency gained from your Student Type. When you use this Skill, you add your Reputation Level to the roll (minimum 1). This is referred to as “Skill Mastery.” Trace a Circle around your Proficiency Diamond.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"MK CH.3 P.37","identifier":"elemental-affinity-water","classIdentifier":"","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rTu0L05QczSz0IN1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674628215003,"modifiedTime":1675796830738,"lastModifiedBy":"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"0zgRFPfPJdowJ8ZE"}
{"name":"Elemental Affinity: Fire (Destructive)","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/fire.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Branching Elements:</strong> Lightning or Toxins</p><p><em>A person in-tune with Fire may be impulsive, open-minded, expressive, humorous, dramatic and a good performer. They usually act with their heart but can be blunt at times.</em></p><p>Your Armor becomes 14 + your Dexterity Modifier (Maximum +2)</p><p><strong>Roll to Resist Proficiency:</strong> Choose one Physical (Strength, Dexterity, Constitution)</p><p><strong>Elemental Affinity (Skill Mastery):</strong> Your connection with your Element empowers you to recognize your strengths and grants confidence in yourself and a Skill. After choosing your Element, choose either a Skill you gained Proficiency in from your Court Card of Fate or one Proficiency gained from your Student Type. When you use this Skill, you add your Reputation Level to the roll (minimum 1). This is referred to as “Skill Mastery.” Trace a Circle around your Proficiency Diamond.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"MK CH.3 P.37","identifier":"elemental-affinity-fire","classIdentifier":"","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rTu0L05QczSz0IN1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674628215003,"modifiedTime":1675796820184,"lastModifiedBy":"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"GfxqokbdVP8mMs9w"}
{"name":"Elemental Affinity: Earth (Solid)","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/mountain.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Branching Elements:</strong> Wood or Metal</p><p><em>A person in-tune with Earth may be practical, disciplined, focused, enjoy routines, be a good leader, and be dependable. Usually they enjoy being in control, but are found to be very loyal.</em></p><p>Your Armor becomes 16</p><p><strong>Roll to Resist Proficiency:</strong> Choose one Physical (Strength, Dexterity, Constitution)</p><p><strong>Elemental Affinity (Skill Mastery):</strong> Your connection with your Element empowers you to recognize your strengths and grants confidence in yourself and a Skill. After choosing your Element, choose either a Skill you gained Proficiency in from your Court Card of Fate or one Proficiency gained from your Student Type. When you use this Skill, you add your Reputation Level to the roll (minimum 1). This is referred to as “Skill Mastery.” Trace a Circle around your Proficiency Diamond.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"MK CH.3 P.37","identifier":"elemental-affinity-earth","classIdentifier":"","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rTu0L05QczSz0IN1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674628215003,"modifiedTime":1675796812834,"lastModifiedBy":"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"fo5PDx425tzDKtCA"}
{"name":"Elemental Affinity: Air (Incorporeal)","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/windmill.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Branching Elements:</strong> Force or Sonance</p><p><em>A person in-tune with Air may be an intellectual, a good communicator, observant, talkative, curious and fickle-hearted. Typically they can be conversational, but also distracted.</em></p><p>Your Armor becomes 12 + Dexterity Modifier</p><p><strong>Roll to Resist Proficiency:</strong> Choose one Physical (Strength, Dexterity, Constitution)</p><p><strong>Elemental Affinity (Skill Mastery):</strong> Your connection with your Element empowers you to recognize your strengths and grants confidence in yourself and a Skill. After choosing your Element, choose either a Skill you gained Proficiency in from your Court Card of Fate or one Proficiency gained from your Student Type. When you use this Skill, you add your Reputation Level to the roll (minimum 1). This is referred to as “Skill Mastery.” Trace a Circle around your Proficiency Diamond.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"MK CH.3 P.38","identifier":"elemental-affinity-air","classIdentifier":"","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rTu0L05QczSz0IN1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674628215003,"modifiedTime":1674628610024,"lastModifiedBy":"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"irLk8aD6gSGQAw8C"}
{"name":"Elemental Affinity: Void (Energy)","type":"subclass","img":"icons/svg/circle.svg","system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Branching Elements:</strong> Light, Dark</p><p><em>A person in-tune with the Void may be someone who is strangely well-balanced in their Personal Element and, as such, is a little of everything. Or it could even be someone who is very disconnected from their emotions— but such a harmful separation from one’s own feelings is typically temporary and self-imposed (whether consciously or subconsciously). To remain in such a state for lengthy periods of time is inherently agonizing for any person, most especially for a Magi-Knight.</em></p><p>Your Armor becomes 14 + your Dexterity Modifier (Maximum +2)</p><p><strong>Roll to Resist Proficiency:</strong> Resist Magic Proficiency</p><p><strong>Elemental Affinity (Skill Mastery):</strong> Your connection with your Element empowers you to recognize your strengths and grants confidence in yourself and a Skill. After choosing your Element, choose either a Skill you gained Proficiency in from your Court Card of Fate or one Proficiency gained from your Student Type. When you use this Skill, you add your Reputation Level to the roll (minimum 1). This is referred to as “Skill Mastery.” Trace a Circle around your Proficiency Diamond.</p><p></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"MK CH.3 P.38","identifier":"elemental-affinity-void","classIdentifier":"","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rTu0L05QczSz0IN1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674628215003,"modifiedTime":1675796825466,"lastModifiedBy":"RJIYZv8z53QKqobo"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"spyevnLgpSWwrtdy"}
